The bytecode for the policy <code>wsh(multi(2, @0/<0;1>/*, @1/<0;1>/*))</code> with the BIP 48 mainnet multisig P2WSH shared origin path <code>m/48'/0'/0'/2'</code> and no fingerprints is the 82-bit stream <code>2052d84212a00182182140</code> (11 bytes; 82 bits used, 6 bits trailing zero-padding from the last byte). Reproducible via the reference CLI: <code>md encode --path "m/48'/0'/0'/2'" 'wsh(multi(2,@0/<0;1>/*,@1/<0;1>/*))'</code> followed by <code>md bytecode &lt;phrase&gt;</code>. Section breakdown (n = 2, kiw = ⌈log₂(2)⌉ = 1):

